race.comment: PATTERA (3) gets his chance in this mediocre affair. Returned to form last start with a very close second in a Class 2 over this trip at Grenfell. Only needs to hold that performance level to give this a mighty shake. CHOOKSTER (7) tackled a $50k picnic race at Dubbo last start and wasn't disgraced at big odds. Worth noting Wendy Peel is back aboard - she has three wins from four rides on this gelding. Ready to peak now at the third run back. SHAQUILA (2) is going well on the picnic circuit including a big win at Geurie two back. Distance specialist who should be in the finish with the help of a perfect draw. THE FAVORITE SON (6) turned in a nice effort when resuming at Leeton last time and can build on that performance. LOCKADENTE (9) returned to form at Grenfell last start and from the inside gate is definitely a contender.
